<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The branch else if (PERF_RPL_PARAM_ONE_CHAR == param_res) abort(); is unreachable. When p[1] != '-' param_res is set by process_short_params_str(), which by its loop never returns PERF_RPL_PARAM_ONE_CHAR (it either returns an error or another result, or PERF_RPL_PARAM_FULL_STR if all characters were processed). When p[1] == '-' param_res is set by process_long_param(), and long-option handlers do not use PERF_RPL_PARAM_ONE_CHAR. Therefore the abort() branch can never be taken, violating MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.1 (no unreachable code).
</scenario>
